parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not receive the necessary protection in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt to lock or function properly can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not be adequately restrained in the event of an accident.

The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the airbag may deploy incorrectly or not deploy at all, resulting in inadequate protection for the driver and passengers.

The failure of the instrument cluster display can cause the driver to be unable to read important information, such as the gear position and outside temperature, which can lead to driver error, accidents, and decreased safety.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is dim
the temperature pixels are not functional
the driver is unable to read the gear position
the driver must squint or take their eyes off the road to read the display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, property damage, and potentially, fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or takes off unexpectedly
even when the brake pedal is applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken throttle linkage cable can cause a loss of acceleration, leading to hazardous situations, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to respond to accelerator input
resulting in a loss of power
causing the vehicle to stall or coast to a stop.
